# Checklist steps — Safety
ChecklistSafetyPowerOff = Confirm unit is powered off before inspection
ChecklistSafetyPowerOffDesc = Ask customer to power off and unplug before remote guidance begins.
ChecklistSafetyExterior = Inspect exterior for damage
ChecklistSafetyExteriorDesc = Cracks, dents, burn marks, or moisture ingress.

# Checklist steps — Power
ChecklistPowerSupply = Verify power supply and outlet
ChecklistPowerSupplyDesc = Confirm correct voltage, working outlet, and undamaged cord.
ChecklistPowerStartup = Power on — observe startup behavior
ChecklistPowerStartupDesc = Note any error lights, unusual sounds, or failure to start.

# Checklist steps — Oxygen compressor specific
ChecklistCompIntakeFilter = Inspect intake filter
ChecklistCompIntakeFilterDesc = Remove and inspect for clogging or saturation. Replace if dirty.
ChecklistCompOutputPressure = Measure output pressure (PSI)
ChecklistCompOutputPressureDesc = Should read within spec. Note actual reading.
ChecklistCompFlowRate = Verify flow rate (LPM)
ChecklistCompFlowRateDesc = Measure LPM at output port. Compare to product spec sheet.
ChecklistCompMoistureTrap = Check moisture trap / desiccant
ChecklistCompMoistureTrapDesc = Inspect color indicator or saturation level. Replace if exhausted.
ChecklistCompOutletPurity = Test outlet oxygen purity
ChecklistCompOutletPurityDesc = Use analyzer if available. Normal is 90–96% O2.
ChecklistCompVibrationNoise = Listen for abnormal vibration or noise
ChecklistCompVibrationNoiseDesc = Rattling, grinding, or high-pitched squealing may indicate piston or valve wear.
ChecklistCompHeatTemp = Check unit temperature after 10-minute run
ChecklistCompHeatTempDesc = Excessive heat on cabinet top or sides may indicate blocked vents or failing components.

# Checklist steps — General
ChecklistCustomerSteps = Review customer-reported steps to reproduce
ChecklistCustomerStepsDesc = Ask customer to describe exactly when the issue occurs.
ChecklistReproduce = Attempt to reproduce the issue
ChecklistReproduceDesc = Walk through the reported scenario step by step.
ChecklistFirmware = Verify firmware / software version
ChecklistFirmwareDesc = Check if unit is on current firmware. Note version.

